FT  10 JAN 94 / Company News (This Week): David S Smith - Other companies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The paper, packaging and office supplies group is expected on Wednesday to
announce a fall in interim profits from Pounds 15.2m to about Pounds 12m.
The reason for the reduction is a further fall in paper prices, the result
of low demand and competition from cheap imports from Germany, as well as
weakness in the corrugated box market. Production has been affected by the
rebuilding of a machine at Smith's Kemsley mill.
