<HEADLINE>
FT  10 JAN 94 / Observer: UN likely
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Business sponsorship window of the moment must be the United Nations' 50th
anniversary, due in 1995 - a 'unique opportunity to reposition the UN' as
the hopeful press release puts it.
No-one would deny the organisation needs a facelift. This week, for
instance, UN sources expect Secretary General Boutros Boutros-Ghali to take
the unusual step of backing the appointment of a special 'force inspector'
for former Yugoslavia. His brief? To hasten investigations into months-old
allegations of black marketeering, prostitution and the transporting of
people from Sarajevo for payment.
</TEXT>
