<TEXT>
Sir, Mr Herbert E Meyer (Letters, January 1/2) argues that the proper role
for government in creating economic growth is to establish ground rules
while entrepreneurs make growth happen.
Perhaps one of the proper roles for government, as automation increases and
the requirement for employees decreases, will be to ensure a reasonably
equitable distribution of those employment opportunities which exist?
