FT  10 JAN 94 / Scott Inquiry to examine UK/Iraq documents
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Scott inquiry is examining documents which suggest that the contribution
of UK manufacturing to Iraq's military enhancement was more widespread than
that suggested by Whitehall and ministers.
An official with the inquiry confirmed yesterday that Lord Justice Scott is
looking at a dossier supplied by The Sunday Times which includes allegations
that Royal Ordnance supplied material to Germany which was eventually
shipped to Iraq.
British Aerospace has denied that it has breached export regulations and is
offering to co-operate fully.
Meanwhile, the inquiry is checking United Nations documents made available
by the government to see if any of those concerning Iraq's nuclear programme
are missing. The inquiry was given information last year which had been
gathered by a UN inspectorate team and was thought to mention the names of
British companies involved.
The Sunday Telegraph yesterday said some of the documents had been
suppressed by the government.
