   By JOHN RIDDING
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
France and Saudi Arabia have agreed to establish a joint committee to
discuss commercial co-operation and finalise industrial and armaments
contracts worth an estimated Dollars 2bn (Pounds 1.34bn), after a visit to
Riyadh by Mr Edouard Balladur, the French prime minister.
