close Nijs en Vale, its wholly owned Dutch subsidiary, later this year
following completion of its existing contracts.
Nijs en Vale, which makes architectural facades mainly in the Netherlands,
incurred estimated operating losses of Fl 2.7m (Pounds 900,000) and an early
return to profitability is not expected.
Closure costs are estimated at Fl 6.5m and about 70 jobs will be affected by
the decis-ion.
Yule Catto's 1993 results will make provision for Nijs en Vale's anticipated
losses and will also reflect a Pounds 1.4m charge in respect of goodwill
which arose on the acquisition and which had previously been set against
reserves.
