FT  08 JAN 94 / Letters to the Editor: Pounds 1m is not happiness for all
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mrs J E BARNES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Backing up R L Webb's letter (January 2) with regard to the proposed
Pounds 1m premium bond prize, I would go further and suggest that this sum
be divided into prizes of Pounds 1,000 each. Surely, like the thoughts of
Micawber, Pounds 1,000 for most equals happiness and Pounds 1m for a few
equal unhappiness all round.
And unless Ernie takes note of public opinion I intend to draw out my not
inconsiderable holding, which until recently attracted a regular prize of
Pounds 50, which encouraged me to buy more.
J E Barnes,
36 Lakeside Park Drive,
Reydon,
Southwold,
Suffolk IP18 6YB
</TEXT>
