   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Saudi Arabia has asked the US to reschedule Saudi payments on around Dollars
30bn of military equipment purchases because of the impact of declining oil
revenues on its budget, US defence officials said yesterday.
A Pentagon spokesman said Prince Bandar bin Sultan, Saudi Arabia's
ambassador to the US, had met US officials in charge of foreign military
sales, as well as top executives from defence contractors, including General
Dynamics, McDonnell Douglas and Hughes Aircraft, to discuss the kingdom's
financial plight.
