manageable and will continue to work toward a resolution on the
restructuring of the programme,' the Pentagon said. 'Programme adjustments
will focus on the timing of production and deliveries of major programme
items.'
With government revenues under pressure from weaker crude oil prices, Saudi
Arabia announced last weekend it would cut spending this year by 20 per cent
in order to curb its persistent budget deficit.
Saudi Arabia's military shopping list includes McDonnell's F-15 fighter,
General Dynamics' Abrams tank and Raytheon's Patriot missile defence system.
